parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Pump Relay Failure due to Rear Seat Bracket Interference
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump relay can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fires. The relay failure can also cause damage to the fuel pump and other electrical components.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or fails to start
burning smell or smoke from the rear fuse block
the fuel pump relay is hot or melted
the fuse block is damaged or melted
the vehicle's electrical system is malfunctioning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause loss of control of the vehicle, leading to accidents or near-misses, especially at low speeds or during rainy weather conditions.
symptoms: Squeaking noise from steering when turning

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clock spring can cause a distraction to the driver's focus, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: Abnormal squeaking sound when turning the steering wheel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause loss of power, leading to accidents or near-misses, especially during sudden stops or crashes.
symptoms: engine turning over without key inserted/FOB pressed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Takata inflators can cause serious injury or death in the event of an accident.
